sql:
SELECT adjustments.adjustment_id, instruments.description, adjustments.factor, adjustments.move_value
FROM adjustments
JOIN instruments ON adjustments.instrument_id = instruments.instrument_id;

SELECT i.*, a.*
FROM instruments i
LEFT JOIN adjustments a ON i.instrument_id = a.instrument_id;

SELECT adjustment_id 
FROM adjustments 
WHERE factor > 5;

external_knowledge:
- 'move_value' reflects changes in market value;
- 'log_move_value' is calculated as the logarithm (base 2) of 'move_value', highlighting the relative impact of adjustments;
- Users who can create adjustments are those with 'can_create' flag set to 1.
